criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  adult patients (≥18 years)

          -  having agreed to take part in the study and complete post-operative follow-up
             requirements (by having signed the information leaflet-informed consent form);

          -  with;

          -  for whom the physician made the decision to implant a Lucidis

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  patient included in an interventional therapeutic trial at the time of inclusion;

          -  patient presenting contraindications for the implantation of an intraocular lens;

          -  patient presenting an ophthalmic disorder liable to interfere with the study
             endpoints;

          -  patient presenting with an astigmatism ≥1.0 D;

          -  patient refusing or unable to comply with the follow-up procedures in the study
             (patient unable to be reached by telephone, liable to be lost to follow-up, etc.);

          -  History of previous intraocular surgery in the study eye in the previous 6 months;

          -  patient is pregnant, breast-feeding or unable to make the decision to participate in a
             clinical investigation (e.g. mentally ill or handicapped person)
